 NFF 2nd Vice President/LMC Chairman Shehu Dikko  Contrary to reports in some medium that the properties of the two high ranking officials of the football governing body in Nigeria were sealed by the ICPC, Rashidat Okoduwa, ICPC spokesperson informed The Guardian that the “properties were marked for investigation.” Dikko, who is also Chairman of the Nigeria League Management Committee (NLMC), has his property located at the high brow Maitama area on River Benue Street. The action of the ICPC followed a Federal High Court order granted yesterday in Abuja. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .